race.comment: DU CLISSON (12) is a progressive mare who has won two on the bounce in impressive style, backed into $1.65 at Warrnambool last time and proving far too good again in a BM66. This is a fair bit harder but she'll carry 54kg after the claim and can continue to progress. Similarly, RHIA (11) has won both starts this time in, too strong under 60kg at Seymour last time out. Back to 1000m is no issue at all, she'll land in a good spot and take beating. MARTIAL MUSIC (1) resumes. He's a consistent sprinter around this sort of level and all five wins have come at 1000m. He'll roll forward and give a sight. RUNLIKENENCRYPTION (7) was good in a handy race at Flemington last time when getting into fourth. She should be able to have last crack at these off a strong tempo.
